{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# S6 — Lock the GitHub repo to a read-only mirror (repo-level ruleset)\n\n## Why\nEnforce that GitHub `main` can ONLY be advanced by the Gerrit replication identity. The\norg is on a free plan, so the lock is a REPO-LEVEL ruleset (admin-proof ORG-level rulesets\nrequire a paid plan). Accepted risk: trusted repo admins can edit/disable a repo-level\nruleset — explicitly accepted for this PoC.\n\n## What\n- REPLACE the existing `main-protection` ruleset (DERISK E5: id 18048287, currently\n  `pull_request` + `required_status_checks` + `deletion` + `non_fast_forward`, admins\n  bypass-via-PR). That ruleset assumes a human PR workflow and is INCOMPATIBLE with the\n  mirror lock — the repo cannot both \"require human PRs\" and \"allow only the deploy key to\n  push\". The mirror lock disables/replaces it.\n- A repo-level ruleset (enforcement Active) on `main` (+ the branch set the bot pushes):\n  Restrict updates + Restrict creations + Restrict deletions + Block force-pushes; bypass\n  list = EXACTLY the replication deploy key in \"Always allow\" mode (added via the REST\n  API / IaC — the UI omits deploy keys as bypass actors).\n- A SEPARATE tag ruleset (`refs/tags/**`) with the same rules + the bot bypass (else tag\n  pushes get rejected).\n- Mirror hygiene: turn OFF Pull Requests (the Feb-2026 repo setting), disable Issues +\n  Actions; add a \"mirror — contribute via Gerrit at rebar.solutions.navateam.com\" banner to\n  the About + README; do NOT archive (archiving freezes the replication bot too).\n- Codify via the Terraform github provider where possible (note the provider's historical\n  DeployKey-bypass gap -> a `gh api` step may be needed for the bypass actor).\n\n## Scope\nIn: the GitHub-side lockdown + mirror hygiene. Out: the Gerrit-side replication (S5).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/terraform/github.tf` and/or a `gh api` script under `infra/github/`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A direct `git push` to `main` (and a PR-merge) by a non-bypass identity is REJECTED;\n      force-push and branch deletion are rejected.\n- [ ] The replication deploy key CAN push `main` and tags (it is the SOLE bypass actor,\n      \"Always allow\", on BOTH the branch and tag rulesets).\n- [ ] Pull Requests and Issues are disabled; Actions disabled; the README/About carries the\n      mirror banner; the repo is NOT archived.\n- [ ] The pre-existing `main-protection` ruleset (PR + required-status-checks model) is\n      replaced/disabled (it can't coexist with \"only the deploy key may push\").\n- [ ] The accepted risk is recorded: the repo-level ruleset is editable by trusted repo admins\n      (free org -> no admin-proof org-level rule). Confirmed: navapbc is a `free` org; Issues are\n      already disabled; 0 deploy keys exist today (S5 adds the replication key)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782686144360827001,"uuid":"571b769c-89e2-4aa9-a253-d01af793c829"}